pageContext.claim: “Mexico is -- is taking people, bringing them back to their country. They're grabbing them and they're bringing it back to their country and I just see an account that just came out that they just sent 15,000 back to their country, 15,000. Now they weren't doing that for any President.”
pageContext.analysis: Mexican government officials say they returned 15,000 Central American migrants over a one-month period, but Trump is wrong to say Mexico was not doing this for any other president. There were more than 2 million Northern Triangle deportations in Mexico from 2001-18.
